On Tue, 30 Mar 1999, Russell Steffen wrote:
> 
> Is anyone using an ICP Vortex RAID controller with a 2.2.5 kernel?
> 
> I'm getting a completely hung machine after inserting the gdth.o module.
> It prints out the first line:
> 
> Configuring GDT-PCI HA at 0/16 IRQ 11
> 
> and the *boom*, the machine locks up solid.
> 
> I checked ICP's site for any driver updates, but the one they have is the
> same code that's in the 2.2.5 kernel. This card works great with the same
> driver (or at least it reports the same version) under 2.0.36.
> 
> Any ideas?
I've got the new driver from ICP vortex yesterday. So far the 2xPPro200/512
machines with miscellaneous GDT controllers behave themselves. They promised
to release this driver to the public in a few days...
